Explanation:

ðŸ§  Algorithm Steps

Start with: 
          low = 0
          mid = 0
          high = n - 1


While mid <= high:
    If nums[mid] == 0 â†’ put it in the 0s section:
        swap nums[low] and nums[mid]
        increment both low and mid

    If nums[mid] == 1 â†’ already in the correct region:
        just increment mid

    If nums[mid] == 2 â†’ put it in the 2s section:
        swap nums[mid] and nums[high]
        decrement high

âš ï¸ do NOT increment mid here, because the swapped element (from high) might still be 0 or 1 and needs to be checked.


class Solution {
    public void sortColors(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int low=0; int mid = 0; int high = nums.length-1;

        while(mid<=high){
            if(nums[mid]==0){
                swap(nums,low,mid);
                low++;
                mid++;
            }

            else if(nums[mid]==1){
                mid++;
            }

            else if(nums[mid]>1){
                swap(nums,mid,high);
                high--;
            }
        }

    }

    public void swap(int[] nums,int i, int j){
        int temp = nums[i];
        nums[i]=nums[j];
        nums[j]=temp;
    }
}
